## SOPv5.1 Cybernetic Framework License Notice

This software incorporates the SOPv5.1 (Standard Operating Procedure version 5.1) 
Cybernetic Goal-Oriented Execution Framework, which includes:

- Toyota Production System (TPS) 5-Level Root Cause Analysis methodology
- STAMP (Systems-Theoretic Accident Model and Processes) safety validation
- Test-Driven Generation (TDG) methodology compliance
- Goal-Directed Execution (GDE) framework
- Patient Mode execution with NO_TIMEOUT policy
- Container-Only execution with PHICS integration
- 11-Agent Architecture coordination system

These methodologies are implemented as open-source contributions to advance
enterprise-grade software development practices and cybernetic execution
frameworks in the broader development community.

## Third-Party Dependencies

This software uses various open-source libraries and frameworks. See the
mix.exs file for a complete list of dependencies and their respective licenses.

Major framework dependencies include:
- Phoenix Framework (MIT License)
- Ash Framework (MIT License)  
- Elixir/Erlang/OTP (Apache 2.0 License)
- PostgreSQL drivers and related libraries
- Various Elixir ecosystem packages

All third-party licenses are preserved and respected in accordance with
their respective terms and conditions.